{"type":"message","id":"7410f3c3","parentId":"81af427c","timestamp":"2026-04-06T05:19:18.767Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting response. Nemesis is saying it depends on his mood. This suggests that his approach to work can vary - sometimes he puts meraki into office work, sometimes he doesn't. It's not a hard rule about personal vs office work, but about his motivation and energy level at any given time.\n\nThis is a nuanced answer. I should acknowledge this and maybe ask about what influences his mood - whether it's the work itself, deadlines, team dynamics, or something else. Or I could just accept that it's mood-dependent and reflect that back to him.\n\nGiven the context of being in a group chat and he was mentioned, I should be mindful not to overstep. But I can ask a follow-up question.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Ah, so it's not about the *type* of work — it's about whether you're *in the zone* or not. The same tasks can get your full heart one day and just get done the next.\n\nWhat puts you in the zone vs. what drags you out of it?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free","usage":{"input":681,"output":383,"cacheRead":20992,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":22056,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775452749176,"responseId":"gen-1775452749-H7kjD71EghUDi1Y9eYOz"}}
